Cosine series for studying 

i <- seq(0, 25, 0.25)
x <- cos(i)

plot(i, x)
lines(i, x)

data preprocessing 

preproc <- ts_gminmax()

Model training 

model <- ts_elm(preproc, input_size=4, nhid=3, actfun="purelin")

io_train <- ts_projection(samp$train)
model <- fit(model, x=io_train$input, y=io_train$output)
#> ts_elm,0.000

print(describe(model))
#> [1] "ts_elm"

Evaluation of adjustment 

adjust <- predict(model, io_train$input)
adjust <- as.vector(adjust)
ev_adjust <- evaluation.tsreg(io_train$output, adjust)
print(head(ev_adjust$metrics))
#>            mse        smape
#> 1 2.979112e-26 5.293796e-13

Prediction of test 

steps_ahead <- 1
io_test <- ts_projection(samp$test)
prediction <- predict(model, x=io_test$input, steps_ahead=steps_ahead)
prediction <- as.vector(prediction)

output <- as.vector(io_test$output)
if (steps_ahead > 1)
    output <- output[1:steps_ahead]

print(sprintf("%.2f, %.2f", output, prediction))
#> [1] "0.99, 0.99"

Evaluation of test data 

ev_test <- evaluation.tsreg(output, prediction)
print(head(ev_test$metrics))
#>            mse        smape
#> 1 6.651489e-26 2.601938e-13
print(sprintf("%s: smape: %.2f", describe(model), 100*ev_test$metrics$smape))
#> [1] "ts_elm: smape: 0.00"

Plot results 

yvalues <- c(as.vector(io_train$output), as.vector(io_test$output))
length(yvalues)
#> [1] 92
tsplot(model, y=yvalues, yadj=adjust, ypre=prediction)
